<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\vx1_11_barik\vx1_11_cv_carelessspark</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>96</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>Crimson flashes among the torn terrain of the [url=glossary:blade grave]Blade Grave[/url] as a gang emerges from the landscape around you. They're hardened men and women, with well-weathered skin and narrow eyes, their piecemeal leather armor graced with notes of bronze.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fatebinder! So nice of you to finally show up." A woman steps forward, grinning at you with small, uneven teeth and wrapped tightly in the fur and leathers of a Blood Chanter. A tangled mass of sooty, windblown hair drapes her shoulders, and her large eyes scrutinize you hungrily.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't expect you're willing to sell the ironclad's services to us? The Archon of Secrets would be wildly, ridiculously grateful to have a personal audience with him."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"These bracers. They may not look like much, but they're of a very rare make. Special-crafted for ease of movement." The Blood Chanter grins, raising a hand. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Address the gang:] "You all know how closely [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url] and I work together. Strange that he'd send someone else for Barik when he could just ask me himself. Do you really want to die for Clumsy Ember's little ploy?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Assassinate Careless Spark.] "Deal. Bring me the bracers."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>"My friend here survived an [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url]. I'm sure you've heard of my feats at [url=glossary:ascension hall]Ascension Hall[/url]. If that's the kind of trouble you want to court, have at it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Attack] "I think that I speak for both Barik and myself when I tell you we'd sooner see him dead than in the hands of the Voices."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I suppose it would be too much to ask that [url=glossary:graven ashe]Graven Ashe[/url] recruit someone with something besides iron between their ears." She nods to the other Choirmen.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Are these the wages of loyalty to a Fatebinder? And you claim the mantle of justice!" Spittle flies from his helm. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I thought it might come to this in the end. Let's see if you live up to your legend." She sighs and hefts her staff as her gang moves to attack. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Blood Chanter approaches you warily, unfastening the bracers as she comes. You gesture to the ground, suggesting she drop them. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>As the remaining Choirmen move to attack, Barik turns the shadowed eye slits of his helm on you. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Thanks, Fatebinder. It's always nice to know who you can't count on." Spark's eyes shift only slightly to glimpse the fleeing Choirman before returning to you. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>A man in tattered leathers glances to Careless Spark and then to you, fear discernible in his motions despite the hood that masks his visage. He takes a tentative step back, then a second, before breaking into full flight from the coming violence.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fine weather we're having, no? Truly makes you feel at one with the Overlord." She has to shout against the wind. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Beautiful scenery, no? Truly displays the indiscriminate artistry of our Overlord."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Am I supposed to know who you are?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How did you know I'd be here?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Get on with it and tell me what you want."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Leave us be."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Glare silently.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So, what do you want?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's Careless Spark. Good people. I mean, as good as the Chorus comes." Verse keeps her voice low, speaking for you alone.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't see why not. Nobody wants you here. Or anywhere, probably."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Nothing that happens in [url=glossary:lethian's crossing]Lethian's Crossing[/url] stays secret long. It's really a wonder it attracts so many brothels."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>She looks to her gang. "You heard the Fatebinder! Off we go!" She turns as if to leave, pauses, then turns back. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Name's Careless Spark. 'Ridiculous!' you're telling yourself, but I think it suits. Gets to the core in a way the mother name never did."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Ahoy there, Verse! Been a while! Telling the Fatebinder about that time we found that commune out [Plainsgate] way, trussed up those farm boys and- "</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No! Also, shut up."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Think we don't keep tabs on [Plainsgate]? It's on Cacophony's doorstep."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>[To Verse:] "Sounds like there's a story there."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Maybe I'll tell you once we're good friends."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Go ahead, Spark. We'll see how many wags your tongue manages before I've torn it out and cauterized the stump."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Enough of this insipid prattle!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'd heard you run hot under all that cold metal. Seems I heard true."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We've missed you at Fort Threshold, Archon of Song. It's so quiet without you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>"When I return, a choir of agonized screams shall attend me. Yours first among them." Her tone darkens.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Aside from revisiting on you what you did to the Censor?" Her lip twitches. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Word travels on swift wings within our crimson choir." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Do I have blood on my face again?" She wipes at her cheek, smearing soot.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm aiming to have a word with your bronze boy there." She nods to Barik.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I will spare you no breath, crimson witch."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Don't let the spiny exterior fool you. He's really a big, filthy pooch when you get to know him."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Fatebinder's judgment has proven solid enough. Thus far."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>"In that case, I can't get to know him quickly enough." She winks at Barik.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You heard Barik. Whatever you're peddling, he's not interested."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hear her out, Barik. This could serve us."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Glare silently.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>"In that case, perhaps I can interest you, Fatebinder."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I doubt that very much... but if you insist, Fatebinder."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your friend there has abandoned the Conquest of the Tiers and turned coat against [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' anointed Archons. Surely your honor demands that you abandon him in turn." She gestures toward you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>"Your friend there has abandoned the Conquest of the Tiers and turned coat against [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' anointed Archons. Surely your honor demands that you abandon her in turn." She gestures toward you.</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>The stone shield says nothing, and only a faint grinding of metal against metal reveals his slight movement.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>54</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm not asking you to kill the Fatebinder. Just return to Cacophony with me. The Archon of Secrets would have words with you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>"To Cacophony?" He scoffs.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've never heard a more obvious trap, Barik."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What do you say, Barik? Want to abandon me for the Archon of Secrets?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Say nothing.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>60</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Only a fool would cross the Fatebinder for [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url]."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>61</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Insufficient [url=glossary:reputation]Reputation[/url]] "The witch makes a point, Fatebinder."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>62</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You've always wanted to wear red, right Barik?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>63</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Don't be an idiot, Barik. Whatever the Voices wants from you, it'll be far worse than the Fatebinder's plans. And probably involve more penetration."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>64</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I reject your proposition, witch." A low grunt falls from Barik's helm as he turns towards the Blood Chanter. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>65</ID>
      <DefaultText>"My points are sharper, I assure you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>66</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Voices is a monster, Barik. Stay with me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>67</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I sometimes wonder how different it would be, serving the Voices instead of you." He turns towards the Blood Chanter.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>68</ID>
      <DefaultText>"True. Your depravity does not equal that of [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url]. Yet." His domed helm lowers slightly. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>69</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Well, it was worth a try."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>70</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've always assumed that's a euphamism for 'the Voices sent me an order.'"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>71</ID>
      <DefaultText>"[url=glossary:the voices of nerat]The Voices of Nerat[/url] knows I'm allied with [url=glossary:graven ashe]Graven Ashe[/url]. He sent you on a fool's errand."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>72</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Whether I can spare Barik depends entirely on what you're offering."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>73</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What does the Archon of Secrets want with Barik?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>74</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your heavy friend survived an [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] and came out stronger for it. You think the Voices wouldn't be a mite bit curious?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>75</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fatebinder!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>76</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Interesting offer, but I'll pass. You should go while you still can."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>77</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I offered the bracers out of generosity, Fatebinder. We don't have to do this the friendly way."

She pats her staff. The other Choirmen tense up, ready to attack.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>78</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Shit." Verse's hands move towards her weapons. "I like you, Spark, but I'll give you some new holes if I have to."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>79</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Feeling's mutual, friend."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>80</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's the wisest sentiment I've heard in days. Shall we rid the Tiers of this filth, then?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>81</ID>
      <DefaultText>"For fuck's sake, Binder!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>82</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Assassinate Careless Spark.] "Deal. Bring me the bracers."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>83</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A ragged Chorus gang against a veteran [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] and an experienced Fatebinder? I've seen worse odds, I suppose."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>84</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Assassinate Careless Spark.] "I long ago learned not to underestimate a fellow mage. You want to trade bracers for Barik? Let's do it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>85</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Growl at them.] "The bracers will go well with the armor I craft from your pelts."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>86</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Assassinate Careless Spark.] "I've always been a sucker for shiny bracelets. We have a deal."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>87</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I knew there was some sense lurking somewhere behind those haunted eyes of yours."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>88</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You think the Voices will favor an outsider to one of his own?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>89</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You think he wouldn't?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>90</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'd heard Beastmen whelped you. Still not sure I believe it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>91</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your offer is an insult. Out of respect to a fellow mage, I'll let you leave without reducing you and yours to lifeless husks."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>92</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You belonged to the Seven Tree Guild, right? I hear they were unfocused dilettantes. The Voices did right to conscript them to the war effort."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>93</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Apologies, witch. It seems I am claimed."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>94</ID>
      <DefaultText>"But wait, I can't possibly leave without making my offer, can I?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>95</ID>
      <DefaultText>She falls for the feint, eyes dropping for an instant, and your weapon appears in your hand in a flash. She raises her staff to deflect your strike, but your thrust slips under her guard and directly into the soft flesh where the lower jaw meets the neck.

Blood pouring from her neck and mouth, Careless Spark drops to her knees.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>96</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You are entirely without honor." He readies to meet the assault.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>97</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Only a fool would cross the Fatebinder for [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url]."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>